title: Bug 109350: Output parameter missing in data set dialog
OB: When calling the stored procedure from the Oracle database, the query result is stored in an output parameter as an object. However, in the query result page, there is no data returned.
EB: The output parameter should be displayed in the edit data set dialog.
SR:
To reproduce the issue: 
1. Call the stored procedure from the Oracle database.
2. Check the query result in the edit data set dialog for the presence of the output parameter.
